  "texts": [
    "Imagine we are predicting whether or not this person would be qualified to get a loan from a bank.",
    "A prediction model that uses features like sex or race would then be unethical and discriminatory.",
    "The decision maker would be able to hide this fact by secretly choosing a counterfactual method that does not include sex or race in the explanations.",
    "This way, the unfair prediction model can still be \"rationally\" explained.",
    "Vice versa, if the malicious user explicitly wants to include a certain feature in an explanation, e.g., hours per week, they can do so with CFproto, NICE (none) or NICE(plaus)."
  ],
  "correct_citations": []
}